

## install gems to local application directory

    bundle install --path vendor/bundle

this will create local bundle copy with gems and evrything needed 

        ▾ bundle/                      
          ▾ ruby/                      
            ▾ 1.9.1/                   
              ▸ bin/                   
              ▸ bundler/               
              ▸ cache/                 
              ▸ doc/                   
              ▸ gems/                                                                                                                     
              ▸ specifications/        
                .DS_Store              
              .DS_Store                
            .DS_Store                  
        ▸ plugins/     

